message.content:
1. Two variants near IRS1, rs1522813 and rs2943641, were genotyped.
2. The genotyping was done in 738 overweight/obese adults.
3. The average age of the adults was 60 years with a standard deviation of 9 years.
4. The average BMI of the adults was 32.7 with a standard deviation of 3.9 kg/m2.
5. The adults were randomly assigned to one of four weight-loss diets.
6. The weight-loss diets involved a deficit of 750 kcal/day of caloric intake from baseline.
7. The weight-loss diets varied in macronutrient contents.
8. The duration of the diet was 2 years.
